+# WasmPlugin – Minimal Rust Filter Example
+
+A minimal proxy-wasm filter in Rust that injects a custom response header.
+
+## Project structure
+
+```
+my-filter/
+├── Cargo.toml
+├── src/
+│   └── lib.rs
+└── Dockerfile
+```
+
+## Cargo.toml
+
+```toml
+[package]
+name = "my-filter"
+version = "0.1.0"
+edition = "2021"
+
+[lib]
+crate-type = ["cdylib"]
+
+[dependencies]
+proxy-wasm = "0.2"
+log = "0.4"
+```
+
+## src/lib.rs
+
+```rust
+use proxy_wasm::traits::*;
+use proxy_wasm::types::*;
+
+proxy_wasm::main! {{
+    proxy_wasm::set_log_level(LogLevel::Trace);
+    proxy_wasm::set_http_context(|context_id, _root_context_id| -> Box<dyn HttpContext> {
+        Box::new(MyFilter { context_id })
+    });
+}}
+
+struct MyFilter {
+    context_id: u32,
+}
+
+impl Context for MyFilter {}
+
+impl HttpContext for MyFilter {
+    fn on_http_response_headers(&mut self, _num_headers: usize, _end_of_stream: bool) -> Action {
+        // Inject a custom header on every response
+        self.add_http_response_header("x-wasm-filter", "active");
+        Action::Continue
+    }
+}
+```
+
+## Dockerfile
+
+```dockerfile
+FROM rust:1.75 AS builder
+RUN rustup target add wasm32-wasi
+WORKDIR /app
+COPY . .
+RUN cargo build --target wasm32-wasi --release
+
+FROM scratch
+COPY --from=builder /app/target/wasm32-wasi/release/my_filter.wasm /plugin.wasm
+```
+
+## Build & publish
+
+```bash
+docker buildx build --platform linux/amd64 -t ghcr.io/my-org/my-filter:v1 .
+docker push ghcr.io/my-org/my-filter:v1
+```
+
+## Apply
+
+```yaml
+apiVersion: extensions.istio.io/v1alpha1
+kind: WasmPlugin
+metadata:
+  name: my-filter
+  namespace: istio-demo
+spec:
+  selector:
+    matchLabels:
+      app: backend
+  url: oci://ghcr.io/my-org/my-filter:v1
+  phase: STATS
+```
+
+## Verify
+
+```bash
+kubectl exec -n istio-demo <frontend-pod> -- curl -v http://backend:9090 2>&1 | grep x-wasm-filter
+# Expected: < x-wasm-filter: active
+```
diff --git a/istio/19_wasm_plugin/wasm-plugin.yaml b/istio/19_wasm_plugin/wasm-plugin.yaml
new file mode 100644
index 0000000..fc88af1
--- /dev/null
+++ b/istio/19_wasm_plugin/wasm-plugin.yaml
@@ -0,0 +1,84 @@
+# Lesson 19 – WasmPlugin: Custom Envoy Filters
+# Extend Envoy's behavior with WebAssembly modules — without recompiling Istio.
+# Filters run inside a sandbox: no host file/network access, safe to deploy.
+#
+# Use cases: custom auth, rate limiting, request transformation, telemetry.
+---
+# ── Example 1: Custom header injection filter ─────────────────────────────────
+# Applies a Wasm module that injects a custom header on every request.
+# The OCI image contains the compiled .wasm binary.
+apiVersion: extensions.istio.io/v1alpha1
+kind: WasmPlugin
+metadata:
+  name: custom-header-injector
+  namespace: istio-demo
+spec:
+  selector:
+    matchLabels:
+      app: backend
+  url: oci://ghcr.io/my-org/header-injector:v1.2.0   # OCI image registry
+  phase: AUTHN                    # Run in authentication phase (before routing)
+  priority: 10                    # Higher = runs first (within the same phase)
+  pluginConfig:                   # Passed to the Wasm module as JSON
+    header_name: "x-wasm-injected"
+    header_value: "true"
+
+---
+# ── Example 2: Custom rate limiter ───────────────────────────────────────────
+apiVersion: extensions.istio.io/v1alpha1
+kind: WasmPlugin
+metadata:
+  name: rate-limiter
+  namespace: istio-demo
+spec:
+  selector:
+    matchLabels:
+      app: backend
+  url: oci://ghcr.io/my-org/rate-limiter:latest
+  phase: AUTHZ                    # Run in authorization phase
+  pluginConfig:
+    requests_per_second: 100
+    burst: 20
+
+---
+# ── Example 3: Custom telemetry / stats enrichment ────────────────────────────
+apiVersion: extensions.istio.io/v1alpha1
+kind: WasmPlugin
+metadata:
+  name: custom-metrics
+  namespace: istio-demo
+spec:
+  selector:
+    matchLabels:
+      app: backend
+  url: oci://ghcr.io/my-org/custom-metrics:v2.0
+  phase: STATS                    # Run in stats phase (after response)
+  pluginConfig:
+    business_metric: "order_value"
+    header_to_extract: "x-order-amount"
+
+# ── Phase execution order ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
+# UNSPECIFIED_PHASE → AUTHN → AUTHZ → STATS
+#
+# Phase    | Purpose                         | Common uses
+# ---------|----------------------------------|-----------------------------------
+# AUTHN    | Before authentication            | Custom token validation, API keys
+# AUTHZ    | Before authorization             | Rate limiting, IP allowlists
+# STATS    | After response, collect metrics  | Business metrics, custom logging
+
+# ── Building a Wasm filter ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
+# Use the proxy-wasm SDK (Rust, Go, C++, AssemblyScript):
+#
+# Rust example:
+#   cargo install wasm-pack
+#   # implement proxy_on_request_headers() in src/lib.rs
+#   wasm-pack build --target web
+#   docker buildx build --platform linux/amd64 -t ghcr.io/my-org/my-filter:v1 .
+#   docker push ghcr.io/my-org/my-filter:v1
+#
+# The WasmPlugin controller pulls the OCI image, extracts the .wasm binary,
+# and distributes it to all matching sidecars via the xDS API (no restart needed).
+
+# ── Verify WasmPlugin is loaded ───────────────────────────────────────────────
+# kubectl get wasmplugin -n istio-demo
+# istioctl proxy-config listener <backend-pod> -n istio-demo -o json | grep wasm
diff --git a/istio/README.md b/istio/README.md
new file mode 100644
index 0000000..098b5d3
